---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About"
	description="What thermoprops.com is, and why it shows its work instead of just returning an answer."
>
	<div class="mb-6">
		<h1 class="font-display text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">About</h1>
	</div>

	<div class="flex max-w-2xl flex-col gap-4 text-text-muted">
		<p>
			thermoprops.com is a fast, transparent property-interpolation reference for
			engineering students working refrigeration, air-conditioning, and thermodynamics
			problems. Look up a saturated, superheated, or two-phase R-134a state, or find a
			state from a known property — every result shows the bracketing table rows and the
			interpolation fraction used to compute it, not just the final number.
		</p>
		<p>
			That's deliberate. Matching a value against a property table by hand — finding the
			right rows, working out the fraction, interpolating — is a specific skill students
			are expected to learn. Hiding those steps behind a single output number would make
			the tool faster but less useful.
		</p>
		<p>
			This is a lookup and interpolation aid, not a homework solver. It won't apply
			compressor efficiencies, choose cycle assumptions, or make the judgment calls that
			are part of the exercise — those stay with the student. What it removes is the
			tedium and error risk of manual table lookup and linear interpolation, so more of
			the effort goes toward the actual engineering.
		</p>
	</div>
</Layout>
